<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 17 at 11:20PM EDT  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...LOCALLY DENSE FOG OVERNIGHT...
Areas of fog will persist overnight across southern New England.
Some of this fog may be locally dense, with visibility of one
quarter mile or less. Dense fog may become more widespread early
Friday morning.
Motorists should exercise caution and be prepared for rapidly
changing visibilities. Slow down and allow extra distance between
vehicles. Also, use low beams in the fog.</description>
